==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Goodly
<hw>Good"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Excellently.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Goodly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Goodly
<hw>Good"ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Goodlier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Goodliest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>godlich</ets>, AS.
<ets>g⟦omac⟧dlic</ets>. See <er>Good</er>, and <er>Like</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Pleasant; agreeable; desirable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We have many <qex>goodly</qex> days to see.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of pleasing appearance or character; comely;
graceful; <as>as, a <ex>goodly</ex> person; <ex>goodly</ex> raiment,
houses.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>goodliest</qex> man of men since born.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Large; considerable; portly; <as>as, a
<ex>goodly</ex> number</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Goodly</qex> and great he sails behind his link.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj></p>

<p><ent>Goodlyhood</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Goodlyhead</ent>⟦br⟧
